<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-17T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-17T12:00:00-05:00" n="827" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d827">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5414c: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Vice Consul at Viborg</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Imbrie</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-17T13:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October 17,
                                        1919—1 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>In case Petrograd falls it is desired that you proceed there as soon as
                            you safely can and cable the Department at the earliest practicable
                            moment a report upon general conditions especially the material needs of
                            the population. It is expected that a part at least of your report will
                            be given to the press here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Adee</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>